Four breathing machines that reportedly went missing in Migori County have been recovered amid a backlash from residents, who are demanding accountability from senior officers in the health department.
This comes barely a day after the Kenya Medical Supplies Authority (Kemsa) released a statement indicating that the county received two ventilators on December 22.



