The agency said the county also received two Continuous Positive Airway Pressure (CPAP) machines in May as part of government donations.
The machines donated by the World Bank in support of the fight against Covid-19 were collected on December 22 by the county’s Health Chief Officer Dalmas Oyugi, according to Kemsa.
The agency further insisted that the two ventilators were collected from its Embakasi Supply Chain Centre, denying implications that the World Bank had donated four.



