Kemsa received the distribution list of the ventilators from Afya House on November 19 and released the two ventilators to Migori County as per the distribution list” read part of the statement by Kemsa.
Investigations
Investigations carried out by the Nation at Migori County Referral Hospital revealed that the county was in possession of 10 ventilators and two CPAP machines sourced from the agencies.
Health Executive Kephas Nyamita and the chief officer, on Wednesday termed the reports of missing equipment as “misleading”, weeks after Governor Okoth Obado took issue with Kemsa “for failing to produce the consignment, months after it was donated by the World Bank”.
On December 21, Mr Obado challenged Kemsa to deliver four ventilators that were donated to the county by the World Bank, noting that the consignments were yet to be delivered to the facility months after they were donated in July.



